    <note type="biography">
        <p>Widow of John Bonham-Carter (died 1838), Whig MP for Portsmouth, 1817–38. Family friend of the Darwins. Resided at Ravensbourne Lodge, Keston, two miles north-west of Down, Kent, from 1853; moved to Keston House by 1862.</p></note>
